Since ``jsyaml`` isn't a bonafide ``Angular`` type of lib, it can't be injected in the component definition of the model, unfortunately.  And it looks like it ALSO doesn't attach itself to ``window`` as a library like ``Mousetrap`` does.  So it looked like the best way to get it globally available was to assign it to a var in the ``entry-index.js`` file.  If you just make that entry look like this:

    window.jsyaml = require('js-yaml');

Then it appears to work everywhere in that ``resultset.js`` and probably anywhere else we'd want it.  Though none of the other entries in ``entry-index.js`` seem to need that, I can't see a reason why this would be bad.  

