@hanno-arm, thanks for your input. It looks that this commit should fix one of two reported problems. I'll try to apply it and check on nRF52 platform.

The second problem is connected with slow ECC calculations. Some platforms calculate ECC in software so slow, that peer times out and retransmits last flight (check sequence diagram in #1207). This retransmission is stored in rx buffer and it is not processed until ECC calculation ends. In this case the node, that was performing ECC calculation, sends duplicated response (the first one is freshly calculated, the second one is triggered by retransmission in receive buffer).
It would be great if mbedtls could send only one response in case there are is a few retransmissions of last flight in rx buffer.

